-- names of drinkers who frequent ONLY bars that serve ONLY beers they like
-- you can find drinkers who frequent bars that serve beers they dislike

WITH dislikes as (SELECT drinker.name as drinker, beer.name as beer
  FROM drinker, beer
  EXCEPT 

  SELECT *
  FROM likes)
  
SELECT name
FROM drinker

EXCEPT
  
SELECT frequents.drinker as name
FROM frequents, dislikes, serves
WHERE frequents.bar = serves.bar and frequents.drinker = dislikes.drinker and dislikes.beer = serves.beer;

WITH
a AS 
(SELECT F.drinker, F.bar, S.beer
FROM frequents F, serves S
WHERE F.bar = S.bar),

b AS 
(SELECT L.drinker, S.bar, S.beer
FROM likes L, serves S
WHERE L.beer = S.beer),

diff AS
(SELECT DISTINCT drinker
FROM ((SELECT * FROM a) EXCEPT (SELECT * FROM b)) AS temp)

SELECT name
FROM drinker
WHERE name NOT IN (SELECT * FROM diff);

column1:
SELECT d.name
FROM (
	(SELECT name from drinker)
	
	EXCEPT ALL
	
(
	SELECT first.drinker
	FROM
	(

		(SELECT frequents.drinker, frequents.bar, serves.beer
		FROM serves, frequents
		WHERE serves.bar = frequents.bar)

		EXCEPT ALL

		(SELECT likes.drinker, frequents.bar, likes.beer
		FROM frequents, likes
		WHERE frequents.drinker = likes.drinker)

	) as first
)

) as d;

select f.drinker, s.beer
  from frequents f, serves s
  where f.bar = s.bar
  
except

  from likes
)

  from drinker d
  where d.name not in (select dont_like.drinker as name from dont_like)

WITH fs AS
(SELECT DISTINCT drinker, frequents.bar AS "bar", beer
FROM frequents
JOIN
serves ON(frequents.bar = serves.bar)),
fl AS
(SELECT DISTINCT frequents.drinker AS "drinker", bar, beer
FROM frequents
JOIN
likes ON (frequents.drinker = likes.drinker)),
diff AS
(SELECT *
FROM fs
EXCEPT
SELECT *
FROM fl)

SELECT name
FROM drinker
EXCEPT
SELECT DISTINCT drinker AS "name"
FROM diff;

With foo as (
Select frequents.drinker,frequents.bar, serves.beer 
From frequents, serves
Where frequents.bar = serves.bar
),

foo2 as (
Select frequents.drinker, frequents.bar, likes.beer
From frequents, likes
Where frequents.drinker = likes.drinker
),

first as (
Select * From foo
Except
Select * from foo2
),

firstdrinkers as (
Select drinker
From first
),

alldrinkers as (
Select name
From drinker
),

final as (
Select * from alldrinkers
Except
Select * from firstdrinkers
)

Select * 
From final

WITH FS AS
	(SELECT drinker AS name, frequents.bar, beer FROM frequents, serves WHERE frequents.bar = serves.bar)
SELECT DISTINCT drinker.name FROM drinker WHERE NOT EXISTS
		(SELECT * FROM FS WHERE FS.name = drinker.name AND FS.beer NOT IN 
			(SELECT beer FROM likes WHERE likes.drinker = drinker.name)
		)

column1:
with leftside(drinker) as
(select name as drinker
from drinker 
),

FreqServ(drinker, bar, beer) as
(select frequents.drinker, serves.bar, serves.beer
from frequents, serves
where frequents.bar = serves.bar
),

likesServ(drinker, bar, beer) as
(select likes.drinker, serves.bar, serves.beer
from likes, serves
where serves.beer = likes.beer
),

rightdif(drinker) as
(select drinker, bar, beer
from  FreqServ

where not exists(

select drinker, bar, beer
from likesServ
where likesServ.drinker = FreqServ.drinker and likesServ.bar = FreqServ.bar and likesServ.beer = FreqServ.beer
)
)


select drinker
from
(select drinker
from leftside

except 

select drinker
from rightdif) as final

WITH drinkerBars AS (
SELECT frequents.drinker, frequents.bar, serves.beer FROM frequents, serves
WHERE frequents.bar = serves.bar
),
drinkerLikes AS (
SELECT likes.drinker, serves.bar, likes.beer FROM likes, serves
WHERE likes.beer = serves.beer
),
difference AS (
SELECT * FROM drinkerBars EXCEPT (SELECT * FROM drinkerLikes)
)

SELECT drinker.name FROM drinker EXCEPT (SELECT difference.drinker FROM difference)

column1:
with negate as
((select distinct f.drinker, s.beer
from frequents f, serves s
where f.bar = s.bar)
except
(select * from likes))

(select d.name 
from drinker d)
except 
(select n.drinker from negate n)

column1:
WITH 
	freserves(drinker, beer) AS
	(SELECT f.drinker, s.beer
	FROM serves s, frequents f
	WHERE s.bar = f.bar),

	differ(drinker, beer) AS 
	((SELECT * FROM freserves)
	EXCEPT
	(SELECT * FROM likes))

(SELECT name FROM drinker)
EXCEPT
(SELECT drinker FROM differ);

with temp1 as (select drinker.name as drinker, beer.name as beer from drinker, beer except select* from likes)
select distinct drinker.name as name from drinker
except
select distinct frequents.drinker as name
from frequents, serves, temp1
where frequents.bar = serves.bar
  and frequents.drinker = temp1.drinker
  and serves.beer = temp1.beer

(SELECT DISTINCT name FROM drinker)
EXCEPT ALL
(WITH Temp1 AS
((SELECT F.drinker, F.bar, S.beer
FROM frequents F, serves S
WHERE F.bar = S.bar)
EXCEPT ALL
(SELECT F.drinker, F.bar, S.beer
FROM frequents F, likes L, serves S
WHERE F.drinker = L.drinker and L.beer = S.beer and F.bar = S.bar))
SELECT DISTINCT drinker as name FROM Temp1);

WITH testC AS
(WITH testA AS
(SELECT DISTINCT l.drinker, s.beer
FROM likes l, frequents f, serves s
WHERE l.drinker = f.drinker AND f.bar = s.bar),
testB AS
(SELECT drinker, beer
FROM likes)
(SELECT * FROM testA a)
EXCEPT ALL 
(SELECT * FROM testB b))
(SELECT name FROM drinker)
EXCEPT ALL
(SELECT drinker FROM testC)

column1:
SELECT name
FROM drinker
WHERE name NOT IN
(
	SELECT DISTINCT l.drinker
	FROM frequents f, likes l, serves s
	WHERE f.bar = s.bar
	AND f.drinker = l.drinker
	AND (l.drinker, f.bar, s.beer) NOT IN
	(
	SELECT DISTINCT l.drinker, f.bar, s.beer
	FROM frequents f, likes l, serves s
	WHERE f.bar = s.bar 
	AND f.drinker = l.drinker
	AND s.beer = l.beer
	)
)

(SELECT L.drinker, S.bar, L.beer
 FROM likes L, serves S
 WHERE L.beer = S.beer),

dBars AS
(SELECT F.drinker, F.bar, S.beer
 FROM frequents F, serves S
 WHERE F.bar = S.bar),

difference AS
(SELECT * 
 FROM dBars
 EXCEPT (SELECT * FROM dLikes))

SELECT D.name
FROM drinker D
EXCEPT (SELECT difference.drinker FROM difference)

WITH temp1 as ((select distinct likes.drinker, beer.name as beer
from likes, beer
where likes.beer != beer.name) except (select * from likes))
select drinker.name
from drinker
where drinker.name not in 
(select distinct temp1.drinker
from serves, temp1, frequents
where serves.beer = temp1.beer and frequents.drinker = temp1.drinker and frequents.bar = serves.bar)

column1:
select *
from 

(select a.drinker
from frequents as a
where a.drinker not in

(select b.drinker
from frequents as b
where not exists 

(select * 
from serves, likes
where b.bar=serves.bar 
and b.drinker=likes.drinker
and serves.beer = likes.beer))) 
as beer_likes

where beer_likes.drinker not in

(select frequents.drinker
from frequents, serves
where frequents.bar = serves.bar
and not exists 

(select * 
from likes

column1:
SELECT name  
FROM drinker 
WHERE name NOT IN (select f.drinker
                  from frequents f, serves s
                  where f.bar = s.bar
                    and not exists (select * from likes l
                                    where f.drinker=l.drinker and s.beer = l.beer));

new as (SELECT f.drinker, f.bar FROM frequents f EXCEPT SELECT drinkerdiffs.drinker, drinkerdiffs.bar FROM drinkerdiffs),

WITH drinker_serves_diff AS (
        SELECT drinker.name, serves.bar, serves.beer
        FROM drinker 
        CROSS JOIN serves
        EXCEPT (        
                SELECT likes.drinker, serves.bar, serves.beer
                FROM likes
                JOIN serves 
                ON serves.beer = likes.beer)
), frequents_minus_non_likes AS (
        SELECT drinker, bar
        FROM frequents
        EXCEPT (
                SELECT name, bar
                FROM drinker_serves_diff
        )
), drinker_frequents_bar AS (
        SELECT name 
        FROM drinker 
        EXCEPT (
                SELECT drinker 
                FROM (
                        SELECT drinker, bar 
                        FROM frequents
                        EXCEPT (
                                SELECT * 
                                FROM frequents_minus_non_likes
                        )
                ) as temp
        )
)

SELECT * FROM drinker_frequents_bar;

WITH Likes2 AS
(SELECT L.drinker, S.bar, L.beer
FROM Likes L, Serves S
WHERE L.beer = S.beer),

Bars2 AS
(SELECT F.drinker, F.bar, S.beer
FROM Frequents F, Serves S
WHERE F.bar = S.bar),

diff AS
(SELECT *
FROM Bars2
EXCEPT 
(SELECT * 
FROM Likes2))

SELECT D.name
FROM drinker D
EXCEPT 
(SELECT diff.drinker
FROM diff)

column1:
(select d.name 
from drinker d)
except
(select SillyDrinkers.drinker as name
from 
  ((select d.name drinker, s.beer, s.bar 
  from serves s, drinker d, frequents f 
  where d.name = f.drinker and s.bar = f.bar)
  except
  (select l.drinker, l.beer, s.bar
  from serves s, likes l, frequents f
  where s.beer = l.beer and s.bar = f.bar)) 
  as SillyDrinkers
);

WITH notLike AS(
	SELECT *
	FROM
	(SELECT drinker.name AS drinker
	 FROM drinker
	) AS drinker
	CROSS JOIN
	(
	SELECT beer.name AS beer
	FROM beer
	) AS beer
	EXCEPT
	(
		SELECT *
		FROM likes
	)
)
SELECT drinker.name
FROM drinker
EXCEPT(
SELECT servesNotLike.drinker
FROM 
(
	SELECT notLike.drinker, serves.bar, serves.beer, serves.price
	FROM serves JOIN notLike ON serves.beer=notLike.beer
) AS servesNotLike 
JOIN frequents ON servesNotLike.drinker = frequents.drinker AND servesNotLike.bar = frequents.bar
)

allCombos as (select name as drinker, beer, bar from serves, drinker),
actualCombos as (select drinker, beer, bar from likes natural join serves),
shouldntGo as (select * from allCombos except select * from actualCombos),
freq as (select drinker, bar from frequents),
badDrinkers as (select * from freq intersect select drinker, bar from shouldntGo)
(select name from drinker) except (select drinker as name from badDrinkers)

barsLiked AS (SELECT L.drinker, S.bar, S.beer FROM likes AS L, serves AS S WHERE L.beer = S.beer),
barsNotLiked AS (SELECT * FROM barsFrequented EXCEPT (SELECT * FROM barsLiked))

SELECT name FROM drinker EXCEPT (SELECT barsNotLiked.drinker FROM barsNotLiked)

with likes_serves as
  (select serves.bar, likes.drinker, serves.beer
  from serves, likes
  where serves.beer = likes.beer),
  frequents_serves as
  (select frequents.bar, frequents.drinker, serves.beer
  from frequents, serves
  where frequents.bar = serves.bar),
  not_bar_drinker as
  (select fs.bar, fs.drinker
  from frequents_serves as fs
  where (fs.bar, fs.drinker, fs.beer) not in (select * from likes_serves))
select distinct drinker.name
from drinker, not_bar_drinker
where drinker.name not in (select not_bar_drinker.drinker as name from not_bar_drinker);

column1:
SELECT name
FROM drinker
WHERE name NOT IN
(SELECT DISTINCT f.drinker
FROM frequents f, likes l, serves s
WHERE f.drinker = l.drinker
AND f.bar = s.bar
AND s.beer NOT IN (SELECT DISTINCT likes.beer
FROM likes

column1:
WITH drinkerBar AS (
    SELECT f.drinker, f.bar, s.beer
    FROM frequents AS f, serves AS s 
    WHERE f.bar = s.bar
),

drinkerLike AS (
    SELECT l.drinker, s.bar, s.beer 
    FROM likes AS l, serves AS s 
    WHERE l.beer = s.beer
),

barDislike AS ( 
    SELECT * 
    FROM drinkerBar 
    EXCEPT (
        SELECT * 
        FROM drinkerLike
    )
)

SELECT d.name 
FROM drinker AS d 
EXCEPT (
    SELECT barDislike.drinker 
    FROM barDislike
)

SELECT name FROM drinker WHERE NOT EXISTS
(SELECT f.bar FROM frequents f, serves s WHERE f.drinker = drinker.name AND f.bar = s.bar AND s.beer NOT IN (SELECT beer FROM likes WHERE drinker = drinker.name));

column1:
WITH Names AS
(SELECT d.name AS drinker FROM drinker d)

SELECT * FROM Names n
  WHERE not EXISTS
    (SELECT * 
    FROM frequents f
    WHERE n.drinker = f.drinker
      and EXISTS
        (SELECT *  
        FROM serves s
          WHERE f.bar = s.bar and not EXISTS
              (SELECT *
              FROM likes l
              WHERE f.drinker = l.drinker AND s.beer = l.beer
)));
